cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SI 

This paper is about word embeddings, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses similarity estimation and outlier detection, which are topics related to machine learning and data mining. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also likely categories. Finally, the paper suggests that rank-based measures can improve clustering quality, which is a topic related to data analysis and unsupervised learning, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible category as well.
